          "content": "Everything builds. Here's a summary of what was done and what was fixed:\n\n---\n\n**What was broken (and fixed):**\n\n1. **Missing `libnxp_transport` in CGo LDFLAGS** — `bindings/go/nxp.go` pointed to `build/src` (non-existent) and omitted the transport library. Fixed to `build_debug/src` + `build_debug/src/transport`.\n\n2. **Thread-safety race** — The C library is single-threaded. The event loop goroutine called `nxp_poll` while `Dial`/`ListenNXP` called into C from another goroutine. Fixed with `nxpMu sync.Mutex` serializing all C calls, with locked/unlocked variants to avoid deadlock in callbacks.\n\n3. **Missed `goOnConnected` for server connections** — By the time `goOnNewConn` registered the callback, the connection was already `ESTABLISHED`. Fixed by checking state immediately in `goOnNewConn` and closing `readyCh` if already established.\n\n4. **`GracefulShutdown` crash** — `nxp_shutdown` was called while the poll goroutine was still running. Fixed by adding `eventLoopDoneCh` and waiting for the goroutine to fully exit. The `nxp_shutdown` call itself was removed since individual `Close()` calls handle cleanup safely.\n\n5. **`Write` + `ShutdownWrite` packet reordering** — Sending data then FIN as separate calls could result in FIN arriving before data (UDP). Fixed by using `WriteFin` (data + FIN in one `nxp_stream_send` call).\n\n6. **`go_echo/main.go` created** — Tests NXP Reliable, Fast, and File streams end-to-end with server echo verification."
